# Agent rules

Read and follow [`docs/rules.md`](docs/rules.md) before significant work. That file is the **sole source of truth** for agent rules; do not contradict it.

Apply it when planning, coding, debugging, adding dependencies, writing tests, or editing nodes and workflows.

## When to re-read `docs/rules.md`

| Task | Sections |
| --- | --- |
| Any significant change | Skim full doc; §1–§10 always |
| Parameter asks / composer copy | §12, §17 |
| Graph paths / expansion | §13, `.cursor/rules/graph-expansion.mdc` |
| Parameter keys / lookup display | §14–§16 |
| Planner inspector / validation | §19–§20 |
| Presentation / transcript / block lifecycle | §21, §25 |
| Center panel block types | §25, `.cursor/rules/center-panel-block-registry.mdc` |
| Feature planning | §22–§23, `.cursor/rules/plan-review-gate.mdc` |
| Equation display trace | §24 |

## Specialized cursor rules (pointers only)

These extend `docs/rules.md` — they do not replace it:

- `.cursor/rules/graph-expansion.mdc` — §13
- `.cursor/rules/parameter-key-consistency.mdc` — §14
- `.cursor/rules/param-composer-metadata.mdc` — §17
- `.cursor/rules/lookup-conditionals.mdc` — §18
- `.cursor/rules/plan-review-gate.mdc` — §22–§23
- `.cursor/rules/paragraph-subsection-naming.mdc` — §11
- `.cursor/rules/feature-planning.mdc` — planning workflow
- `.cursor/rules/center-panel-block-registry.mdc` — center panel scroll block types (§25)

For feature plans and non-trivial changes, include **Architecture Consistency Review** (§23) and **Plan Review Gate** (§22) per `plan-review-gate.mdc` before writing production code.
